comments: Nunn (LAL) moves alongside Bane's (MEM) path and marginal contact occurs as they disengage during the driving shot attempt. Nunn makes clean ball contact on his block attempt as Bane maintains control throughout and a jump ball is correctly called.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) establishes himself in Schroder's (LAL) path and does not deliver illegal contact as he goes under the pick.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) and James (LAL) mutually engage and immediately disengage as marginal contact occurs during the rebound.

Brooks (MEM) is moving laterally when he initiates contact with Westbrook's (LAL) body, which affects his driving shot attempt. A shooting foul is correctly called as Westbrook is gathered on a play that originates outside of and would end inside the LDB when the illegal contact occurs.
Nunn (LAL) makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Jones (MEM) prior to incidental follow-through contact occurring.
Nunn (LAL) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Jones' (MEM) arm during his dribble.
Morant (MEM) reaches for the ball and marginal contact occurs as he brushes Nunn's (LAL) arm during his dribble up the court.
Clarke (MEM) moves laterally into Schroder's (LAL) path and initiates body contact, which affects Schroder's SQBR during the drive.
Nunn (LAL) reaches across Jones (MEM) and makes contact with his body, which affects his SQBR.
Clarke (MEM) jumps alongside Westbrook (LAL) with his arms vertical and absorbs the incidental contact as he legally contests Westbrook's (LAL) play at the basket.
James (LAL) places his arm against Bane (MEM) as both players elevate for the rebound, but the marginal contact does not dislodge Bane from his position.
Schroder (LAL) maintains a legal guarding position and incidental contact occurs as Morant (MEM) spins away at the end of the drive.
Westbrook (LAL) legally contests Morant's (MEM) shot near the basket.
Morant (MEM) reaches for the loose ball and marginal contact occurs with James' (LAL) arm, which does not affect his ability to maintain control of the rebound.
James (LAL) rests his hands on Clarke's (MEM) body and does not apply force as they engage during the rebound.
Jackson Jr. (MEM) legally contests James' (LAL) jump shot attempt.
Brown Jr. (LAL) and Clarke (MEM) both make clean contact with the ball, which causes it to become loose. Any follow-through body contact after the rebound gets dislodged is deemed incidental.
Clarke (MEM) jumps alongside Westbrook (LAL) and marginal body contact occurs during Westbrook's shot near the rim.
Westbrook (LAL) moves laterally into Jones' (MEM) path and initiates body contact, which affects Jones' SQBR as he moves up the court.
Bryant (LAL) is in the lane for less than three seconds when the shot is imminent.
Williams (MEM) is not vertical when he makes contact with Schroder's (LAL) arm and head, which affects his driving shot attempt.
Schroder's (LAL) forearm makes clean contact with the ball and dislodges it away from Bane (MEM) prior to incidental follow-through contact occurring.
Bane (MEM) is trailing when he moves into and initiates contact with Schroder's (LAL) body, which affects his SQBR during the driving shot attempt.
Westbrook (LAL) moves alongside Morant's (MEM) path and collapses his forearm in to absorb the marginal contact before elevating to contest the driving shot attempt.
Gabriel (LAL) moves into and dislodges Clarke (MEM) from his rebounding position, which affects his ability to pursue the loose ball.
Westbrook (LAL) steps inside the three-point arc prior to the release of Clarke's (MEM) free throw attempt.
Westbrook (LAL) briefly rests his arm on Adams' (MEM) body without extending it and marginal contact occurs during the rebound.
Bane (MEM) steps out of bounds prior to elevating on his jump shot attempt. After review, it is confirmed that there are 0.4 seconds left on the clock after the out of bounds violation.
